# AskOps — Cursor Rules
# These rules apply to every file Cursor generates in this project.

## Project
AskOps by AskOps by RaveMinds
Build-in-public LinkedIn project — zero cost, all open source.

## Stack
- Python 3.11
- Mistral 7B via Ollama (local LLM — never use OpenAI)
- LangGraph for agent orchestration
- MCP (Model Context Protocol) for tool connectivity
- LanceDB for vector storage (local, embedded)
- n8n for data pipelines (Docker)
- Langfuse for AI tracing (Docker)
- FastAPI for API gateway
- Slack Bolt for bot interface
- Redis for caching
- Docker Compose for all services

## Non-negotiable rules
- NEVER use OpenAI, Anthropic, or any paid LLM API
- NEVER hardcode secrets — always use python-dotenv
- All data sources are mocked in mock_data.py
- One file = one responsibility
- Every function has a docstring
- Use Pydantic for all request/response models
- Use structlog for all logging — never use print()
- Type hints on every function signature
- Handle errors gracefully — never let exceptions crash the bot

## Trade IDs for mock data
12345 = Trade Failure (settlement timeout)
22222 = Duplicate Trade
33333 = System Outage
44444 = Slow Settlement (SLA breach)
55555 = Risk Engine Rejection

## File responsibilities
mock_data.py          — all mock data, never modified by other files
storage/lancedb_store.py — LanceDB read/write only
ingestion/ingest.py   — populates LanceDB from mock_data
mcp_servers/*.py      — one MCP server per data source
agent/graph.py        — LangGraph agent, calls MCP tools
api/main.py           — FastAPI, calls agent only
bot/slack_bot.py      — Slack Bolt, calls API only
